eshcore-dev/MeshCore> </a></div></div></div></div>"], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1479521241290506331", "author": "TechnoPappy", "author_handle": "technodad68", "user_id": "427956510241325058", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/427956510241325058/63031ca48ca3f7ff42931353eefaf5a4.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, March 6, 2026 11:49 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-06 11:49 a.m.", "text": "Yes, I have an E290 that I’d love to use with MC. However, I’m not technically adept enough to know how to build the firmware, although it seems to be supported. Thanks for the reply.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Yes,   I have an E290 that I’d love to use with MC.  However,  I’m not technically adept enough to know how to build the firmware,  although it seems to be supported.  Thanks for the reply.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/497518225156866052/4075fd35bfa15b0be9b3b54d409a5cbc.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=kastasmykolas>Kamiccolo</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1479455474675093805')\"> It is supported, I presume:\n<a href=\"https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/blob/main/boards/heltec_e290.json\">https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/blob/main/boards/heltec_e290.json</a>\n\nI don&#39;t see it on the list of official builds. Do you need any help building it yourself? </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1480617774127517780", "author": "Kamiccolo", "author_handle": "kastasmykolas", "user_id": "497518225156866052", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/497518225156866052/4075fd35bfa15b0be9b3b54d409a5cbc.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, March 9, 2026 1:26 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-09 1:26 p.m.", "text": "Well, if You like, I'll try building it tonight Will update with the results.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Well, if You like, I&#39;ll try building it tonight <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\"> Will update with the results.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=heart><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=❤️ src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/2764.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/427956510241325058/63031ca48ca3f7ff42931353eefaf5a4.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=technodad68>TechnoPappy</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1479521241290506331')\"> Yes,   I have an E290 that I’d love to use with MC.  However,  I’m not technically adept enough to know how to build the firmware,  although it seems to be supported.  Thanks for the reply. </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1480620845729583387", "author": "TechnoPappy", "author_handle": "technodad68", "user_id": "427956510241325058", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/427956510241325058/63031ca48ca3f7ff42931353eefaf5a4.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, March 9, 2026 1:38 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-09 1:38 p.m.", "text": "Thank you for the offer. Fortunately I found a build yesterday and it’s working great!", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Thank you for the offer.  Fortunately I found a build yesterday and it’s working great!</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/497518225156866052/4075fd35bfa15b0be9b3b54d409a5cbc.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=kastasmykolas>Kamiccolo</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1480617774127517780')\"> Well, if You like, I&#39;ll try building it tonight <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\"> Will update with the results. </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1480669658607784099", "author": "Kamiccolo", "author_handle": "kastasmykolas", "user_id": "497518225156866052", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/497518225156866052/4075fd35bfa15b0be9b3b54d409a5cbc.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, March 9, 2026 4:52 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-09 4:52 p.m.", "text": "Made a fork on github, added separate action to build only E290 firmwares: https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/compare/main...kamiccolo:MeshCore:main The result: https://github.com/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0 So, if you have GitHub account, You could fork it for Your own use Basically it requires few things: synchronize with the upstream (one button click on web interface) create new tag (according to upstream, few more clicks) initiate build (a few more clicks) And after 7 minutes - fresh set of binaries", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Made a fork on github, added separate action to build only E290 firmwares:\n<a href=\"https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/compare/main...kamiccolo:MeshCore:main\">https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/compare/main...kamiccolo:MeshCore:main</a>\n\nThe result:\n<a href=\"https://github.com/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0\">https://github.com/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0</a>\n\nSo, if you have GitHub account, You could fork it for Your own use <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"🙂\"\n    title=\"slight_smile\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f642.svg\"> \n\nBasically it requires few things:\n<ul><li>synchronize with the upstream (one button click on web interface)</li></ul><ul><li>create new tag (according to upstream, few more clicks)</li></ul><ul><li>initiate build (a few more clicks)</li></ul>\nAnd after 7 minutes - fresh set of binaries <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"🙂\"\n    title=\"slight_smile\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f642.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": ["<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=chatlog__embed-color-pill style=background-color:rgba(30,35,39,255)></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-content><div class=chatlog__embed-text><div class=chatlog__embed-title><a class=chatlog__embed-title-link href=https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore/compare/main...kamiccolo:MeshCore:main><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">Comparing meshcore-dev:main...kamiccolo:main &#183; meshcore-dev/MeshCore</div></a></div><div class=chatlog__embed-description><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">A new lightweight, hybrid routing mesh protocol for packet radios - Comparing meshcore-dev:main...kamiccolo:main &#183; meshcore-dev/MeshCore</div></div></div><div class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-container><a class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-link href=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/x3xINeOzwlR1rxmw_2Fh8jDB1X4r4ZWtCj8cL10HJoQ/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/1079bb33ac2bedc13d050e114664edf5cadfbfb15506c6afe43f78dfd7a5f773/meshcore-dev/MeshCore> <img class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail src=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/x3xINeOzwlR1rxmw_2Fh8jDB1X4r4ZWtCj8cL10HJoQ/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/1079bb33ac2bedc13d050e114664edf5cadfbfb15506c6afe43f78dfd7a5f773/meshcore-dev/MeshCore alt=Thumbnail loading=lazy data-canonical-url=https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1079bb33ac2bedc13d050e114664edf5cadfbfb15506c6afe43f78dfd7a5f773/meshcore-dev/MeshCore> </a></div></div></div></div>", "<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=chatlog__embed-color-pill style=background-color:rgba(30,35,39,255)></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-content><div class=chatlog__embed-text><div class=chatlog__embed-title><a class=chatlog__embed-title-link href=https://github.com/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">Release Companion Firmware v1.14.0 &#183; kamiccolo/MeshCore</div></a></div></div><div class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-container><a class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-link href=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/nlpxgVbBuqb0PbYHDZm8YKLzPXDEidXK5tM-_l2ntfM/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/725ffe42e8f7fb163903173ffd9d4d67b5d14806fdac2884ccd73923951e7ded/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0> <img class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail src=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/nlpxgVbBuqb0PbYHDZm8YKLzPXDEidXK5tM-_l2ntfM/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/725ffe42e8f7fb163903173ffd9d4d67b5d14806fdac2884ccd73923951e7ded/kamiccolo/MeshCore/releases/tag/v1.14.0 alt=Thumbnail loading=lazy data-can